HEADWORD: Electro-puncture
<hw>E*lec`tro-punc`ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An operation that consists in inserting needless
in the part affected, and connecting them with the poles of a galvanic
apparatus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

